# Zeabur Netlify-style headers file. Applied at deploy time to override
# the upstream nginx Content-Type for matching paths.
#
# Why we need this — `tokenboss.co/skill.md` is served as a static asset
# from `frontend/public/skill.md`. Default nginx mime.types has no entry
# for `.md`, so it falls back to `application/octet-stream`, which makes
# every browser force-download the file instead of rendering it inline.
# Forcing `text/plain` makes the browser display the raw markdown source
# as readable text (no download). Agents fetching the file via curl /
# `Accept: */*` are unaffected — they consume bytes regardless of MIME.

/*.md
  Content-Type: text/plain; charset=utf-8
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
